## the actual proof structure

間

        MAGNITUDE 0.95
        CERTAINTY 0.85

        Theorem: π₁(S¹) ≅ ℤ

        Proof:
        1. S¹ ≃ₜ ℝ/2πℤ (AddCircle homeomorphism)
        2. ℝ is simply connected (contractible)
        3. ℤ acts on ℝ by n · x = x + 2πn
        4. action is free (n · x = x ⟹ n = 0)
        5. action is properly discontinuous (integer translates)
        6. π₁(X/G) ≅ G for simply connected X, free proper G-action
        7. therefore π₁(S¹) ≅ ℤ ∎

        step (6) is the key lemma
        either Mathlib has it, or we build it (~50 lines)
        
        ◊

